<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="431" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1624,1821]" pageId="0" pageNumber="431">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,264,1625,1648]" pageId="0" pageNumber="431">Remarks:</emphasis>
The name &quot; 
<taxonomicName authority="Mabille" authorityName="Mabille" box="[393,760,1624,1648]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pupinidae" genus="Pseudopomatias" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Architaenioglossa" pageId="0" pageNumber="431" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="balansai">
<emphasis box="[393,667,1624,1648]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="431">Pseudopomatias balansai</emphasis>
Mabille
</taxonomicName>
&quot; was found on labels in The Natural History Museum, London. We were not aware that Mabille had described a species under this name, and speculated that the name 
<taxonomicName box="[1293,1385,1659,1683]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pupinidae" genus="Pseudopomatias" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Architaenioglossa" pageId="0" pageNumber="431" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="balansai">
<emphasis box="[1293,1385,1659,1683]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="431">balansai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was derived from 
<taxonomicName authority="Mabille, 1886 (Pall-Gergely et al. 2015)" authorityName="Mabille, 1886 (Pall-Gergely et al." authorityYear="2015" box="[306,1036,1693,1718]" class="Gastropoda" family="Diplommatinidae" genus="Diplommatina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Architaenioglossa" pageId="0" pageNumber="431" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="balansai">
<emphasis box="[306,564,1693,1717]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="431">Diplommatina balansai</emphasis>
Mabille, 1886 (
<bibRefCitation author="Pall-Gergely" box="[750,1028,1693,1718]" pageId="0" pageNumber="431" refString="Pall-Gergely, B., Feher, Z., Hunyadi, A. &amp; Asami, T. (2015) Revision of the genus Pseudopomatias and its relatives (Gastropoda: Cyclophoroidea: Pupinidae). Zootaxa, 3937 (1), 1 - 49. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3937.1" type="journal article" year="2015">
Páll-Gergely 
<emphasis box="[899,959,1693,1718]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="431">et al.</emphasis>
2015
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Examination of the three 
<typeStatus box="[1343,1436,1694,1717]" pageId="0" pageNumber="431">syntypes</typeStatus>
(
<collectionCode box="[158,241,1729,1752]" country="France" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" name="Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="0" pageNumber="431">MNHN</collectionCode>
<collectionCode box="[253,295,1729,1752]" pageId="0" pageNumber="431">IM-</collectionCode>
2000-31807, 
<figureCitation box="[443,514,1729,1752]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1961,1983]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1360,1940]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,1360,1940]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lectotype (MNHN IM- 2000 - 32496, Fig. B) and paralectotypes (MNHN IM- 2000 - 31807, Figs A and C) of Mellaca balansai Mabille, 1889 (synonym of Pseudopomatias amoenus Möllendorff, 1885). Scale bar = 10 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264131/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="431">Figs 2</figureCitation>
A–C) in the Muséum national d’Histoire naturelle in Paris revealed that 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="431">
Mellaca 
<taxonomicName box="[151,243,1763,1787]" class="Gastropoda" family="Diplommatinidae" genus="Diplommatina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Architaenioglossa" pageId="0" pageNumber="431" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="balansai">balansai</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Mollendorff, 1885" authorityName="Mollendorff" authorityYear="1885" box="[447,943,1763,1787]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pupinidae" genus="Pseudopomatias" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Architaenioglossa" pageId="0" pageNumber="431" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="amoenus">
<emphasis box="[447,728,1763,1787]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="431">Pseudopomatias amoenus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mollendorff" box="[740,943,1764,1787]" pageId="0" pageNumber="431" refString="Mollendorff, O. F. von (1885) Diagnoses specierum novarum sinensium. Nachrichtsblatt der Deutschen Malakozoologischen Gesellschaft, 11 - 12, 161 - 170." type="book chapter" year="1885">Möllendorff, 1885</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Two shells had yellowish, and one reddish colouration. The smaller yellowish shell is hereby selected to be the 
<typeStatus box="[880,978,1798,1821]" pageId="0" pageNumber="431">lectotype</typeStatus>
(
<collectionCode box="[992,1075,1798,1821]" country="France" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" name="Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="0" pageNumber="431">MNHN</collectionCode>
<collectionCode box="[1082,1124,1798,1821]" pageId="0" pageNumber="431">IM-</collectionCode>
2000-32496; 
<figureCitation box="[1266,1331,1798,1821]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1961,1983]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1360,1940]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,1360,1940]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lectotype (MNHN IM- 2000 - 32496, Fig. B) and paralectotypes (MNHN IM- 2000 - 31807, Figs A and C) of Mellaca balansai Mabille, 1889 (synonym of Pseudopomatias amoenus Möllendorff, 1885). Scale bar = 10 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264131/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="431">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
